
0) Test templates in ptfs/chem

1) Build a simple 1D finite difference code.
   Use directory ptfs/grid1D, namespace Grid1D
   Use simple relaxation and Newton-Raphson iterators.
   Classes: Simulation (has System, Domain, Iterator)
            Domain
            Iterator
            Polymer 
            Propagator

2) Build a 1D pseudospectral code for periodic 1D functions.
   Use directory ptfs/periodicPs, namespace Periodic.
   Classes: Simulation (has System, UnitCell, Basis, Iterator)
            UnitCell
            Basis
            Iterator
            Polymer
            Propagator

   Start with RelaxationIterator and NewtonRaphsonIterator

3) Generalize periodic code to 2D and 3D, via templates if possible.

4) Add approximate NR Iterator, AndersonIterator.

5) Add code for symmetry adapted basis functions.

6) Add stress calculators.
